/*!
\page string_lower LOWER Convert strings to lower case

<p>
Section: \ref sec_string "String Functions"
\section Usage
The <tt>lower</tt> function converts a string to lower case with
the syntax
\verbatim
   y = lower(x)
\endverbatim
where <tt>x</tt> is a string, in which case all of the upper case
characters in <tt>x</tt> (defined as the range <tt>'A'-'Z'</tt>) are
converted to lower case.  Alternately, you can call <tt>lower</tt>
with a cell array of strings
\verbatim
   y = lower(c)
\endverbatim
in which case each string in the cell array is converted to lower case.
\section Example
A simple example:

\if FRAGMENT
frag_string_lower_000.m
0
lower('this Is Strange CAPitalizaTion')
\endif


\verbinclude frag_string_lower_000.m.out 

and a more complex example with a cell array of strings

\if FRAGMENT
frag_string_lower_001.m
0
lower({'This','Is','Strange','CAPitalizaTion'})
\endif


\verbinclude frag_string_lower_001.m.out 

